   "body" : "### Describe the issue\r\nCurrently there is no timezone feature to set in bitcoin-qt so that it sets bitcoind to use it.\r\nI see in debug.log that the log times are 2 hours early than my current timezone.\r\n\r\nIve heard that you could maybe create bitcoin.conf and manually put in the timezone but i havent tried anything like that yet because im not sure how to.\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\nA feature option should be available in the bitcoin-qt settings to be able to set the user's timezone correctly.\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\nRight now no timezone option is available.\r\n\r\n### What version of bitcoin-core are you using?\r\nUbuntu 16.04 PPA\r\n\r\n### Machine specs:\r\n- OS: Ubuntu 16.04\r\n",
